End-to-end Natural Language Processing (NLP)
  1. text cleaning: removing puntuations, numbers, stopwords and HTML tags, stemming
  2. text tokenizing and creating a bag-of-words model
  3. word scoring: binary, count, frequency, Term frequencyâ€“Inverse document frequency (TF-IDF)

Examples:
  1. crowdflower airline twitter sentiment data   https://www.crowdflower.com/data-for-everyone/
  2. kaggle IMDB sentiment analysis data    https://www.kaggle.com/c/word2vec-nlp-tutorial
  3. kaggle Yelp business rating data   https://www.kaggle.com/c/yelp-recsys-2013
  4. UCI Spam Collection data   https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/SMS+Spam+Collection
  5. UCI Yelp restaurant review data    https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/Sentiment+Labelled+Sentences#
  6. UCI Amazon product review data   https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/Sentiment+Labelled+Sentences#
